LAUNCHDARKLY.name: LaunchDarkly
LAUNCHDARKLY.tagline: Giving engineering teams control over feature releases with confidence and precision
LAUNCHDARKLY.overview: LaunchDarkly is a feature management platform founded in 2014 by Edith Harbaugh and John Kodumal. The company raised $200M at $3B valuation in August 2021 led by Lead Edge Capital. Revenue reached $60M in 2024 with projections of $70-100M for 2025. LaunchDarkly serves 30 billion feature flags daily to 5,500+ organizations including 25% of Fortune 500. Co-founder Edith Harbaugh returned as CEO in 2024 after briefly stepping down in 2022. Acquired Highlight in April 2025.

LATTICE.name: Lattice
LATTICE.tagline: Helping companies build engaged, high-performing teams through continuous performance management
LATTICE.overview: Lattice is a people management platform founded in 2015 by Jack Altman and Eric Koslow. The company provides performance management, engagement surveys, goals/OKRs, and career development tools. In January 2024, Sarah Franklin (ex-Salesforce CMO/President) became CEO. Lattice serves 5,000+ customers including Slack, Gusto, Monzo, and Discord. In October 2024, Lattice launched its HRIS and AI Assistant at Lattiverse. Revenue reached $137M in 2024. The company's AI Agent Plus launched in 2025 provides personalized coaching and 1:1 support.

LINEAR.name: Linear
LINEAR.tagline: Streamlining software development with fast, beautiful issue tracking built for modern teams
LINEAR.overview: Linear is a modern issue-tracking and project management tool built for software development teams, founded in 2019 by former Airbnb, Coinbase, and Uber engineers. The company focuses on speed, simplicity, and the execution part of development. In June 2025, Linear raised $82M Series C led by Accel at $1.25B valuation after achieving 280% revenue growth. The platform has won marquee AI clients with its lean, user-centered product. Previous investors include Sequoia, founders of Slack, Vercel, and Supercell.

LOVABLE.name: Lovable
LOVABLE.tagline: Enabling anyone to build full-stack software applications through conversational AI
LOVABLE.overview: Lovable is a Stockholm-based AI app builder founded in 2023 by Anton Osika and Oliver Edholm. The platform lets anyone build full-stack software by chatting with AI. Lovable reached $100M ARR in under one year—one of the fastest in history. In July 2025, the company raised $200M Series A at $1.8B valuation led by Accel. By November 2025, secondary market valuations hit $5B+. ARR doubled from $100M to $200M in just four months. Total funding: $228M.
